post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of all drugs could make people live and learn life as it is. Bad decisions are a part of life.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Psychedelics are often used for [one-off, recreational and spiritual](https://www.livescience.com/61902-psychedelic-drugs-change-personality.html) experiences. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Regulations that prohibit working under the influence of alcohol can trivially be expanded to include all drugs. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Controlled substances, while controlled, are still obtained through the black market. Whether it is a date-rape drug or marijuana, legislation still cannot control whether illegal drugs are illegally obtained. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "A high level of correlation does not indicate which of the variables is the cause and which is the effect. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's important to have a standardized quantity of an active substance of controlled quality to prevent overdosing unwanted effects. I think all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalisation of drugs could lead to better education on how to be safe around them. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The additional tax revenue from drug commerce can be used to fund therapies and treatments. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Selling harmful products is a poor long-term business strategy, as can be seen with tobacco companies. It only works as long as there is uncertainty in their harms. When the harms become apparent, people will take measures to stop using it as well as take measures to stop others from using it.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalising drug use would not significantly increase the consumption of drugs. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A [Constitutional Amendment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eighteenth_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution) had to be voted on for the prohibition of alcohol. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Various currently illegal drugs have valuable medical properties; these substances may have the potential to solve problems in our society such as mental health issues. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The logic of this argument would necessitate prohibition of alcohol, along with cigarettes, prescription painkillers, household cleaning products, motor vehicles, power tools; and anything a person may use to end their life consciously or accidentally. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Based on countries that have decriminalized drugs like [Portugal](https://borgenproject.org/decriminalization-of-drugs-in-portugal/), drug use has not significantly increased among the poor population, or at all.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Affordable drugs will more likely lessen the negative impacts of drug use, as overall users would be less likely to abuse substances due to psychological distress caused by financial instability.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "The ability to alter another person's mind state has potential for abuse, and utter manipulation. As a result, people will be more able to infringe on the bodily freedom/autonomy of others."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "A society where everyone consumes moderate amounts of drugs wouldn't be much different than the societies of today. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If drugs other than alcohol were legalized, alcohol sales would plummet, and a lot of jobs in the alcohol industry would disappear.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Illegal drug producers and dealers use violence against police and competition. This just doesn't happen in legal businesses. The causes for this is also obvious. A legal business using violence will get fines and possibly be banned from participating in the legal market, and as such is a non-starter. I believe all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug legalisation will make it easier to carry out [sexual assaults](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug-facilitated_sexual_assault).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "When weed was legalized in Colorado for recreational use, the [usage rate](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-colorado-marijuana-idUSKCN0Z702N) among teens and children stayed the same. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'People would prefer less addicting drugs, so as to lessen the risk of taking them. This would lead to companies to develop less addictive drugs as well.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Criminals will have to either adapt or lose the income that prevents their other crimes from catching up with them.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'People may drive under the influence of drugs or make other decisions with public consequences.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Children of drug addicts would have a much higher chance of receiving the appropriate help if drug users did not have to hide.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The government specifies what is unacceptable through prohibition. Taxation is how the government discourages. The government is only "encouraging" if they provide aid or assistance.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Governments would be able to check what cutting agents are used within the drugs, meaning they will be safer as potentially harmful cutting agents would be banned. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'While some might overestimate the revenue, there still will be revenue. If it is 1/2 or 1/3 of those naive estimates, it is still revenue, and it still increases the government coffers.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Although social prejudice may remain, addicts could seek help far easier if there were no fear of legal repercussions.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Former inmates are significantly more at risk of drug-related mortality than the general population.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs will help treat addicts. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs hinders scientific and, in particular, medical progress.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs has led to medical discrimination.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Criminals will have to either adapt or lose the income that prevents their other crimes from catching up with them.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The consumption of psychoactive substances creates religious and transcendental [experiences](https://www.sciencealert.com/how-religion-led-to-humanity-s-love-for-drugs): both are a relevant part of human evolution and significantly shaped human culture. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Pharmaceutical companies could double their revenues by selling harmful and addictive drugs to begin with and subsequently curing medication.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many poor people use drugs as a temporary escape from poverty [\\(Scottish Drugs Forum, p. 12\\)](http://www.dldocs.stir.ac.uk/documents/drugpovertylitrev.pdf). Criminalization of this behavior does not help them.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is not fair to solve such a problem by prohibiting heroin use for everyone. It should be solved as a problem on its own. This could mean anything from forbidding heroin addicts to have children \\(or parents to use heroin\\), to forming organisations for helping such families. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will lead to increased import/export options for medicines/drugs that are only available overseas and that were banned in the domestic market. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "It can also cause users to mix alcohol with other drugs, which [endangers users' health](https://www.northpointwashington.com/blog/dangers-mixing-alcohol-drugs/) even more."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Drug trafficking](https://www.cnbc.com/2013/08/09/Organized-crime:-Worlds-most-lucrative-criminal-activities.html?slide=1) is the most lucrative form of illicit business, worth about $2.1 trillion per year.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[In 2017](https://www.kialo.com/all-drugs-should-be-legalized-7100/7100.0=7100.1+7100.297), there were more direct deaths from alcohol consumption than from drug consumption.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Under the influence of drugs, users are more likely to commit immoral acts.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'One solution for recreational availability of such drugs could be to require that they emit an unmistakable coloring or odour/taste when dissolved in a drink.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Cocaine is [highly addictive](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cocaine_dependence) and easy to become dependent on. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'People would prefer less addicting drugs, so as to lessen the risk of taking them. This would lead to companies to develop less addictive drugs as well.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'According to [Human Right Watch](https://www.hrw.org/news/2013/06/04/americas-decriminalize-personal-use-drugs), subjecting people to disproportionate criminal sanctions for the personal use of drugs "infringes on their autonomy".'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Incarceration of drug users impacts their families.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "In Uruguay, possession of drugs for personal use [is legal](https://www.tni.org/es/node/16660). That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If the pursuit of freedom and promotion of liberty are goals of a state, then the laws surrounding drug use are incompatible with freedom and liberty.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help patients by facilitating access to medicines \\(drugs\\) that are currently hard to obtain. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The correlation between drug use and crime is fuelled at least partly by prohibition.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In Holland, [a channel](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCvRQKXtIGcK1yEnQ4Te8hWQ) exists just to raise awareness of drugs. It explains how and when to take them, and what to do when a friend is having an OD.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug users are detained along with violent criminals.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Economic hardship resulting from drug use would be better addressed by spending money on treatment, rather than attempting to control supply. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs will create jobs \\(i.e. people selling in certified shops, people in labs etc.\\).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many drugs that are currently illegal have been and are important social tools.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Non-violent dangers could increase, such as syringes being left in parks and other public spaces. This would create a risk of disease and injury to anyone in the area, especially children. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In Colorado, between 2014 and 2017, [over $500 million](https://money.cnn.com/2017/07/19/news/colorado-marijuana-tax-revenue/index.html) in government revenue was raised by taxes and fees on marijuana sales. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Shooting galleries](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supervised_injection_site) could be provided by the government as a safe environment for those requiring them. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The criminalization of drug use is the major agitator of the economic rifts caused by drug use: illegal drug use leads to arrests which lead to arrest records and the socially imposed inability to self-produce wealth.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Through education, heavy advertising campaigns and controlling the packaging of tobacco, the government can make its negative effects clear despite it being legal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is not mutually exclusive with legalizing drugs. Both could be done. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In 2014, [8.7%](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-healthcare-costs-smoking-idUSKBN0JX2BE20141219) of all healthcare spending in the US was spent on tobacco-related illnesses.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Marijuana use in the Netherlands has [not increased](https://www.opensocietyfoundations.org/voices/safe-and-effective-drug-policy-look-dutch) following decriminalisation; in fact, cannabis consumption is lower compared to countries with stricter legislation such as the UK.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If a government wanted to put money into harm reduction, it could do so without legalising drugs in order to avoid the costs of enforcing a drug prohibition. It could instead cut other government programs.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If drugs were legalized, the prison system would be less over-crowded, which is a [significant issue](https://www.prisonpolicy.org/reports/pie2019.html) in the US.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug cartels will not cease their activities if drugs are legalised. They will simply move to other areas to keep their profits \\(drugs for children, black market drugs, human trafficking\\). So drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs are already [easy to get](https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/drugs-buy-how-easy-buy-ice-cream-takeaway-cocaine-crack-marijuana-a8142191.html).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[The use of psychoactive substances](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3202501/) has been a part of human culture for thousands of years; drugs have been used for religious, medical or recreational purposes.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Without help some conditions could [worsen](https://deserthopetreatment.com/co-occurring-disorders/going-untreated/) to the point where they're a danger to others. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The evidence provided in this claim stems largely from importing cheaper cigarettes from the rest of Europe to the UK. The difference in quality is probably minimal. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The same applies to already legal alcohol. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Other factors contribute to the opioid crisis significantly more than the legality of currently prescribed opioids. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Drug legalization will stimulate local and national economies. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalisation of drugs will improve overall safety by containing criminal opportunities.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '"Profit for companies" is better than "profit for criminal cartels", if those are the two choices.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Criminalization \\(and incarceration\\) causes lasting harm to a person's health and life outcomes."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legal cultivation/production of psychoactive compounds on the personal or even community scale could eliminate the international black market for them, making society safer for communities.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is not a matter of being "viewed as" criminals: under a regime of criminalisation, drug users *are* criminals. It is not a matter of "feeling comfortable" seeking help, it\'s that seeking help would no longer carry the threat of actually going to prison. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If the pursuit of freedom and promotion of liberty are goals of a state, then the laws surrounding drug use are incompatible with freedom and liberty.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'One can imagine that an inebriated cannabis user may leave the house less often and therefore spend less money. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Professional addiction treatment is usually [expensive](https://www.addictioncenter.com/rehab-questions/cost-of-drug-and-alcohol-treatment/). I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Currently, in many countries, stores which sell age-restricted products such as alcohol have strict regulations in place to ensure the consumer is of appropriate age. The same could be done with other drugs. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Criminalising the activity of drug users has negative effects on individuals, their families, and society. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is no way to determine in advance what the additional resources/revenue will be used for by the government. It may not be earmarked for harm reduction. So drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug prohibition consumes a considerable portion of public spending.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Pharmaceutical companies could double their revenues by selling harmful and addictive drugs to begin with and subsequently curing medication.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug prohibition has been used as a racist policy to mass incarcerate people of color.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The additional tax revenue from drug commerce can be used to fund therapies and treatments. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The anxiety induced by the threat of arrest can be a cause for the violent paranoia episodes some users experience while under the influence emotion enhancing substances.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If only leaving syringes was punishable, and not use or possession of drugs, they would put in the extra effort to _not_ break the law at all. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A large portion of the public is irresponsible. Giving everyone the opportunity to use \\(or abuse\\) drugs would have negative consequences on these individuals.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The additional tax revenue from drug commerce can be used to fund therapies and treatments. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Prohibition does not treat addicts, treatment, and prevention of addiction do. Both of these are accomplished far more effectively without the threat of incarceration for merely admitting use. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug addiction and abuse are more related to mental health than legality. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Since everything is legal, users can instead choose the drugs with the most benefits and the least harms.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If recreational drugs were legal, social events such as parties would have more variety. Drug-friendly events would also have no cause for paranoia. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalized, users could be required to carry safe containers for syringes.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A part of the "forbidden fruit" effect is that drugs provide short-term benefit \\(the "high"\\) in exchange for long-term cost \\(negative health impacts\\).'}
